{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 3",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-607021007093367351 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/c598f3-79/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=604377810366104239&sectionId=607021007093367351)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggX8JEL8fCf_text","label":"ggX8JEL8fCf_text","default":"You Got Braces To Fix Your Teeth. But Some Treatments May Have Unintended Structural Effects. Dentist Probably Damaged Your Skull."},{"type":"html","id":"ggor7kGraL-_text","label":"ggor7kGraL-_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\"><strong>Here's what happened:</strong></span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Your orthodontist straightened your teeth. But to do that, they had to change your bite in a way that most likely damaged your skull.&nbsp;</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">What you didn't know: Your skull operates like a balloon with 29 interconnected bones. When your orthodontist compressed your dental structure, they likely deflated that balloon.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">And when the balloon deflates, everything inside collapses.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">And that's when the real problems start</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggdhahSmBqf_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggdhahSmBqf_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/bae9e017d8ce3c1a4a3dee522680c31d7b1f9464.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDcqEtwral_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggDcqEtwral_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/851930ca66ce31a899a699ab530bd93596946988.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggjVFZ-f1q2_text","label":"ggjVFZ-f1q2_text","default":"How Certain Dental Changes May Affect Structural Space Over Time: The Curve of Spee"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUWx6FTrjk_text","label":"ggUWx6FTrjk_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Your teeth have a natural curve called the Curve of Spee. This curve isn't random—it's engineered.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">The curve reflects the health of the skull in our view. Orthodontics will often flatten this curve either intentionally or unintentionally</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">This isn't theoretical. We have hundreds of people in our community that did braces and got:</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw5SyJIsl0_text","label":"ggw5SyJIsl0_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Jaw tension or facial tightness</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Changes some people associate with reduced clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Disrupted sleep patterns</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Shifts in posture and overall alignment</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Changes in facial aesthetics over time</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggqxfir1zgx_text","label":"ggqxfir1zgx_text","default":"You're Not Crazy. Your Health Didn't<br>Randomly Decline."},{"type":"html","id":"ggX6Gl7rClt_text","label":"ggX6Gl7rClt_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">If you got braces and then noticed:</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You felt a shift in your daily energy or mental clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You noticed gradual changes in your overall well-being over the years</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You felt your facial aesthetics were changing prematurely</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Your physical drive or performance didn't feel the same</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- You noticed a shift in your general mood and ease</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">... you weren't imagining it. There is a connection.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Most traditional approaches focus primarily on the teeth, often overlooking the broader impact on jaw positioning.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">But thousands of people are now connecting the dots, and the pattern is undeniable.</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggj9eXNZ_zV_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggj9eXNZ_zV_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/adb94291ef899f874f876c38f04e3f103efc0d27-Picsart-AiImageEnhancer.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggCpMlV4Kwa_text","label":"ggCpMlV4Kwa_text","default":"There's a Way to Support Stuctural Space: Gradual Expansion Support"},{"type":"html","id":"ggW6c5vCIMc_text","label":"ggW6c5vCIMc_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Reviv doesn't straighten teeth the way braces do. It supports natural facial balance and encourages structural integrity.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Reviv works on a different principle than orthodontics.</span><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">Rather than traditional methods, Reviv focuses on providing vertical support to your bite:</span></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrwGxsfgrx_text","label":"ggrwGxsfgrx_text","default":"<p><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports your jaw in finding its natural, optimal position.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Encourages space and positioning that may have &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;changed over time..</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports more natural breathing patterns.</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">- Supports overall well-being and mental clarity</span><br><br><span style=\"font-size:15px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
